3:00 PM Defendant Gregory M. Swanson appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Chris Gramstrup present in court on behalf of Defendant. Attorney Tara Marie Jenswold in court for State of Wisconsin. Court calls case. Acknowledges receipt of complaint, has not reviewed and discussed with client, asks for an adjourned initial hearing. Address confirmed. 
State recommends $25,000 cash bail. Anticipates additional charges will be filed. Conditions of no alcohol, no contact with Victim's family or occupants in vehicle. 
Attorney Gramstrup indicates community ties, rental properties, 27 year resident of Douglas County. No prior criminal history. Not a flight risk. Asks for $10,000 to 15,000 cash, no objection to no alcohol and no contact with Victim's family or occupants in vehicle. 
Court must consider a number of factors. Court makes statements. Court orders $15,000 cash bail, with conditions of no alcohol, no driving without valid permit or license and no contact with victim's family or occupants of vehicle.
Initial appearance scheduled for July 26, 2022 at 02:00 pm.
